.TH TCP.H 3HEAD "Sep 10, 2004"
.SH NAME
tcp.h, tcp \- definitions for the Internet Transmission Control Protocol (TCP)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
#include <\fBnetinet/tcp.h\fR>
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The <\fBnetinet/tcp.h\fR> header defines the following macro for use as a
socket option at the \fBIPPROTO_TCP\fR level:
.sp
.ne 2
.na
\fB\fBTCP_NODELAY\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 15n
Avoid coalescing of small segments.
.RE

.sp
.LP
The macro is defined in the header. The implementation need not allow the value
of the option to be set with \fBsetsockopt()\fR or retrieved with
\fBgetsockopt()\fR.
